title: What Kenny Rogers' Ex-Wife Has To Say About Dolly Parton
tags: nicki swift|nickiswift|kenny rogers|dolly parton|kenny rogers dolly parton|kenny rogers about dolly parton|what kenny rogers says about dolly parton|kenny rogers wife|kenny rogers ex wife|kenny rogers ex wife dolly parton|what kenny rogers ex wife has to say about dolly parton|kenny rogers dolly parton truth|dolly parton and kenny rogers|kenny rogers gf|dolly parton husband|dolly parton ex husband|dolly parton partner|kenny rogers partner
description: Country music fans lost a legend on March 20, 2020, when singer-songwriter Kenny Rogers died at age 81. Fans and celebrities alike paid tribute to the icon, including the Texas native's longtime friend and collaborator, Dolly Parton. Parton wrote on Instagram,You never know how much you love somebody until they're gone. I've had so many wonderful years and wonderful times with my friend Kenny, but above all the music and the success I loved him as a wonderful man and a true friend. Fellow country star Reba McEntire commented on her post, quote, Dolly, he sure loved you.Not only did Rogers and Parton share a lot of love, they also worked together on various projects. From the duo's 1985 concert film, Kenny Rogers and Dolly Parton: Together, to their hits like Islands in the Stream, they were an unstoppable force. In fact, the two were so in sync that relationship rumors dogged them for years.Some might assume this topic was uncomfortable for Rogers' five ex-wives, some of whom spoke out after the country crooner's passing. This includes Marianne Gordon, Rogers' fourth wife and mother to his son, Christopher Cody Rogers.Marianne Gordon, an actor, was married to Kenny Rogers from 1977 to 1993. During this time, Gordon got to know the country legend on a deep level, especially where it concerned his close friendship with Dolly Parton. When asked by Closer Weekly about the romance rumors on March 24, shortly after Rogers' death, she replied, I never felt uncomfortable at all. I just knew him so well. But, it's funny that you say that. We had a tennis pro who traveled with us, Doug Dean asked me too. I told him Kenny said I like her as a friend and we have a great thing on stage. We'd lose it. There is sexual tension and teasing each other and it would screw it up.Although Gordon is pretty sure nothing happened between the collaborators, she doesn't rule it out. She added,Dolly might have [made a move though]. It's entered my mind because she always said she thought like a man. I don't mean it badly. Dolly is a fun girl.For those who might not believe Marianne Gordon's account of Dolly Parton and Kenny Rogers' relationship, they should probably take note of a 2013 interview the two did with ABC News. When asked directly whether they were an item at one point, the Jolene singer replied, It never crossed our minds because he was with people. I've been married, forty, I've been with my husband 48 years.Rogers joked, I think that chemistry and that connection comes from an unrequited love, if you will, because we never consummated anything.At the end of the day, the pair's story begins and ends with friendship. Parton told CMT's Cody Alan in 2017,Kenny's friendship means more to me than our hit records. Actually, we're kind of like soul mates. He's from Texas and I'm from Tennessee. There's an old famous country song, 'T for Texas, T for Tennessee.' We always sing that to each other. She added, I love his singing. I love his voice. I never tire of hearing him sing. And I think our voices blend great, so I'm really proud of the musical part of that as well.Of course, it's completely reasonable to have a platonic soulmate. And we think this perfectly explains why Dolly Parton and Kenny Rogers never dated.Watch the video to see What Kenny Rogers' Ex-Wife Has To Say About Dolly Parton.#DollyParton #KennyRogers #RIPKennyRogersRead Full Article: https://www.nickiswift.com/198211/what-kenny-rogers-ex-wife-has-to-say-about-dolly-parton/

description: VAN LIFE AFRICA DURING PANDEMIC | We had to ABANDON OUR VAN & take a RESCUE FLIGHT back to Canada | Join us for our 21 day workout challenge on Eamon & Bec PLUS https://bit.ly/2Umw1o5 ‚ñ∫ CLICK TO SUBSCRIBE so you never miss a video http://bit.ly/2DDSUgu ‚ú® Keep healthy by feeling your body with healing foods like our handmade chai blend (packed with immune boosting spices). Shop our chai here: https://www.chaiwalachai.comFriends featured in today‚Äôs van life vlog:Lee https://www.instagram.com/leemacmil/After an incredible 3 years of living, working and travelling in our self converted Sprinter Van we‚Äôve had to make the very tough decision to abandon our tiny home in Africa to take a rescue flight back to Canada.  As it has for so, so many of us, this global pandemic has absolutely flipped our world upside down. What went from a virus that seemed far away in China, quickly made it‚Äôs way across the globe forcing us to quarantine in our 60 sq-ft in Morocco. And while quarantining was going well for us it became apparent that things would be different for a long while.  When our Prime Minister announced that he was sending repatriation flights over to Africa to pick up Canadians who were stuck (due to border closures) we consulted with friends and family closest to us and realized that in this time of crisis we should be back in our home country. The gravity of what we‚Äôve just done hasn‚Äôt quite sunk in and we ((especially me (Bec)) are having a really hard time adjusting to our new reality.  Having said that we think the most important thing we can all do now is STAY HOME, keep healthy with healing foods & try to look at this as a time that we (and the planet) desperately needed to reset and realign.  Sending each of you so much love throughout this time x‚ú≥ Eamon & Bec Products ‚ú≥‚Ü† our handmade chai blends https://chaiwalachai.com/ ‚Üû‚Ü† our plant-based cookbook https://www.eamonandbec.com/weekday-whip-ups ‚Üû‚Ü† our beautiful photo filters https://www.eamonandbec.com/presets ‚ÜûTour the renovations we've done to our self converted sprinter van:VAN TOUR after 2 years living in our TINY HOUSE on wheels http://bit.ly/newvantourOVERLANDING AFRICA IN OUR SPRINTER VAN has been the adventure we‚Äôve always hoped it would be but it‚Äôs hard to predict what happens next. In fact, we are still processing everything that has happened over the last week and continues to happen... No one knows where we will end up, where our beloved tiny home on wheels will make it or for how long this pandemic will take over life as we know but all we can do is try to remain positive and move forward in the direction that feels right for us. title: How The U.S. Fell Dangerously Behind In Coronavirus Testing
tags: CNBC|business|news|finance stock|stock market|news channel|news station|breaking news|us news|world news|cable|cable news|finance news|money|money tips|financial news|Stock market news|stocks|Coronavirus economic stimulus bill|coronavirus outbreak pandemic|coronavirus lockdown|coronavirus flights|coronavirus stock picks|coronavirus vaccine|coronavirus business
description: The deadly coronavirus pandemic has stopped the world in its tracks, and exposed a weak spot in the United States‚Äô preparedness for a public health emergency. Experts say aggressive diagnostic testing is essential in order to learn where and how an epidemic spreads. But in the critical first weeks of the outbreak in the U.S., one problem after another prevented doctors, clinics, and labs around the country from testing enough people. Patients in America were being sent home as hospitals rationed their test supply, while other countries like South Korea found a way to test hundreds of thousands of people quickly. Now, the U.S. is months behind in understanding the true scope of the virus.
